      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, i think i got that backwards. if shrinkage is high, shouldn't the COGS go up because we're essentially losing money on those items? also, can you give me a quick example? say we started with $500k in inventory and ended with $450k, but we had $20k in shrinkage. how does that change the turnover math specifically?",
